If you haven't played this yet, what are you even doing? It has everything!

)Zombies, zombie dogs, zombie birds, zombie BEARS! some spit at you, some are radiated, some explode, some do all three

)Guns, attachments, ammo types, armor piercing, explosive arrows, M60 machine gun! 

)Base defense, generators, powered doors and switches, electric fences, spikes, giant spinny blades! 

)Don't feel like defending your base when the horde comes? build a helicopter and fly away!

)Survival, crafting, looting, farming, hunting, recipes, skill points, skill books, build variety, strategy, fully customizable settings with 6 levels of difficulty for noobs and masochists alike. Or even turn on creative mode and play it like a sandbox.

)FULLY DESTRUCTIBLE ENVIRONMENT. Every block of entire cities can be broken. Don't feel like going the normal way? take a fireaxe and make your own door! let zoms chew your base too long? it'll fall down around you! Yearn for the mines like a proper dwarf? dig into the side of a mountain and build an underground kingdom!
)Active and creative mod community. get bored of zombies? turn them into robots, or demons, add new vehicles, add new weapons, add new maps or make your own random gen map.

Are there any cons to this game? 

)It is still in early access, so when new alphas drop you'll probably have to start fresh.
)If you want to increase the amount of zombies you fight during hordes, you'll have to sacrifice some graphics unless you're rocking a high end PC. i'm able to play this on a pretty basic laptop, but on mostly low settings. 
)There's not much in the way of story to this game. The traders have a few lines of dialogue, you wake up with a note from "the duke", but beyond building your base and surviving the hordes, there's not a plot or quest-line to follow. you'll have to role-play with just your imagination, or play multiplayer if you want some company.

All in all? 7 days is easily in my top 5 games of all time. Its core game-play scratches a certain itch in my brain, an itch for hoarding bullets and splitting zombie skulls :p. If you haven't tried it you're missing out!
